Class SokobanTile

java.lang.Object
com.aoopproject.games.sokoban.model.SokobanTile
All Implemented Interfaces:
GameEntity
public class SokobanTile extends Object implements GameEntity
Represents a single tile on the Sokoban game board. It implements GameEntity and holds information about its base type (wall, floor, target) and any occupant (player, box, or none). It determines its visual representation based on this state, loading images from the "/sokoban/images/" resource path.

    • isEmpty

      public boolean isEmpty()
      Checks if the tile is considered "empty" in terms of its static base structure. A tile is structurally empty if its base type is not a SokobanBaseType.WALL.

      Note: This method only considers the tile's fundamental type (wall or passable space). The actual ability for an entity (like a player or a box) to move onto or occupy this tile is determined by more detailed game logic within the game model (e.g., in SokobanModel), which also considers the tile's current SokobanOccupant and the specific rules of movement or pushing.

      Specified by:
      isEmpty in interface GameEntity
      Returns:
      true if the tile's base type is not SokobanBaseType.WALL, false if it is a wall (and thus structurally not empty).

      public String toString()
